      \n<style>\n#banner-705271386 {\n  padding-top: 200px;\n  background-color: rgb(255,255,255);\n}\n#banner-705271386 .bg.bg-loaded {\n  background-image: url(https:\/\/ifp.center\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/lucerne-android-iphone-desktop-hd-backgrounds-wallpapers-1080p-4k-wc5k5-1332x850-1.jpeg);\n}\n#banner-705271386 .overlay {\n  background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);\n}\n#banner-705271386 .ux-shape-divider--top svg {\n  height: 150px;\n  --divider-top-width: 100%;\n}\n#banner-705271386 .ux-shape-divider--bottom svg {\n  height: 150px;\n  --divider-width: 100%;\n}\n<\/style>\n  <\/div>\n\n\n\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\t\n<style>\n#section_888788012 {\n  padding-top: 0px;\n  padding-bottom: 0px;\n}\n#section_888788012 .ux-shape-divider--top svg {\n  height: 150px;\n  --divider-top-width: 100%;\n}\n#section_888788012 .ux-shape-divider--bottom svg {\n  height: 150px;\n  --divider-width: 100%;\n}\n<\/style>\n\t<\/section>\n\t\n\t<section class=\"section\" id=\"section_493820127\">\n\t\t<div class=\"bg section-bg fill bg-fill  bg-loaded\" >\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\t\n\n\t\t<div class=\"section-content relative\">\n\t\t\t\n\t<div id=\"gap-2034114325\" class=\"gap-element clearfix\" style=\"display:block; height:auto;\">\n\t\t\n<style>\n#gap-2034114325 {\n  padding-top: 30px;\n}\n<\/style>\n\t<\/div>\n\t\n<div class=\"row align-middle\" style=\"max-width:90%\" id=\"row-614495221\">\n\n\t<div id=\"col-506752956\" class=\"col medium-6 small-12 large-6\"  data-animate=\"flipInX\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-inner\"  >\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t<div class=\"img has-hover x md-x lg-x y md-y lg-y\" id=\"image_401762510\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"img-inner dark\" >\n\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https:\/\/ifp.center\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/260715.jpeg\" class=\"attachment-original size-original\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ifp.center\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/260715.jpeg 1920w, https:\/\/ifp.center\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/260715-300x188.jpeg 300w, https:\/\/ifp.center\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/260715-1024x640.jpeg 1024w, https:\/\/ifp.center\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/260715-768x480.jpeg 768w, https:\/\/ifp.center\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/260715-1536x960.jpeg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<style>\n#image_401762510 {\n  width: 100%;\n}\n@media (min-width:550px) {\n  #image_401762510 {\n    width: 100%;\n  }\n}\n<\/style>\n\t<\/div>\n\t\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\n\n\t<div id=\"col-1979154167\" class=\"col medium-6 small-12 large-6\"  data-animate=\"flipInY\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-inner\"  >\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n<h3 class=\"uppercase\">THE 5 STAGES OF SWISS DEBT RECOVERY<br \/>\n<\/h3>\n\t<div id=\"gap-677432172\" class=\"gap-element clearfix\" style=\"display:block; height:auto;\">\n\t\t\n<style>\n#gap-677432172 {\n  padding-top: 30px;\n}\n<\/style>\n\t<\/div>\n\t\n<p>International Fraud Prevention Center provides a dedicated fixed fee service across all four main stages of the Swiss debt recovery process, including Letter Before Action (LBA), Issuing Court Claims, obtaining a County Court Judgment (CCJ), Enforcement of a CCJ, and additionally if necessary Insolvency Proceedings.<br \/>Our research shows that on average, 86% of cases result in payment at the letter before the action stage, with no further action being required. You can learn more about the subsequent steps in the process that follow the sending of a Letter Before Action below.<\/p>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\n<style>\n#col-1979154167 > .col-inner {\n  padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\n}\n@media (min-width:550px) {\n  #col-1979154167 > .col-inner {\n    padding: 0px 10% 0px 10%;\n  }\n}\n<\/style>\n\t<\/div>\n\n\t\n<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\t\n<style>\n#section_493820127 {\n  padding-top: 30px;\n  padding-bottom: 30px;\n}\n#section_493820127 .ux-shape-divider--top svg {\n  height: 150px;\n  --divider-top-width: 100%;\n}\n#section_493820127 .ux-shape-divider--bottom svg {\n  height: 150px;\n  --divider-width: 100%;\n}\n<\/style>\n\t<\/section>\n\t\n\t<section class=\"section\" id=\"section_79201753\">\n\t\t<div class=\"bg section-bg fill bg-fill  bg-loaded\" >\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\t\n\n\t\t<div class=\"section-content relative\">\n\t\t\t\n<div class=\"row\" style=\"max-width:90%\" id=\"row-481750145\">\n\n\t<div id=\"col-1617446353\" class=\"col small-12 large-12\"  data-animate=\"fadeInRight\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-inner\"  >\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n<h3 class=\"uppercase\">\nTHE STAGES OF DEBT RECOVERY<\/h3>\n\t<div id=\"gap-1338776453\" class=\"gap-element clearfix\" style=\"display:block; height:auto;\">\n\t\t\n<style>\n#gap-1338776453 {\n  padding-top: 30px;\n}\n<\/style>\n\t<\/div>\n\t\n\n\t\t<div class=\"tabbed-content\">\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<ul class=\"nav nav-line nav-vertical nav-uppercase nav-size-normal nav-left\"><li class=\"tab active has-icon\"><a href=\"#tab_the-5-stages-debt-recovery\"><span>THE 5 STAGES DEBT RECOVERY<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<li class=\"tab has-icon\"><a href=\"#tab_letter-before-action\"><span>LETTER BEFORE ACTION<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<li class=\"tab has-icon\"><a href=\"#tab_legal-claim\"><span>LEGAL CLAIM<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<li class=\"tab has-icon\"><a href=\"#tab_county-court-judgment-(ccj)\"><span>COUNTY COURT JUDGMENT (CCJ)<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<li class=\"tab has-icon\"><a href=\"#tab_enforcement\"><span>ENFORCEMENT<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<li class=\"tab has-icon\"><a href=\"#tab_insolvency\"><span>INSOLVENCY<\/span><\/a><\/li><\/ul><div class=\"tab-panels\"><div class=\"panel active entry-content\" id=\"tab_the-5-stages-debt-recovery\">\n<div class=\"row\"  id=\"row-2043778034\">\n\n\t<div id=\"col-787888779\" class=\"col medium-4 small-12 large-4\"  data-animate=\"bounceInLeft\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-inner\"  >\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n<h4>LETTER BEFORE ACTION<\/h4>\n<p>Before issuing any legal proceedings a letter before action (LBA) should be sent to a debtor. An LBA can be sent for as little as $1.50 plus VAT and on average, 86% of cases result in payment at this stage.<\/p>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\n\n\t<div id=\"col-72314960\" class=\"col medium-4 small-12 large-4\"  data-animate=\"bounceInLeft\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-inner\"  >\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n<h4>LEGAL CLAIM<\/h4>\n<p>If you send a letter before action to your debtor but you do not receive a satisfactory response then the next stage in the legal process is to issue legal proceedings through the County Court. The debtor will be sent a court form requiring them to pay the debt, plus interest and costs within 14 days.<\/p>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\n\n\t<div id=\"col-567411088\" class=\"col medium-4 small-12 large-4\"  data-animate=\"bounceInLeft\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-inner\"  >\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n<h4>COUNTY COURT JUDGMENT (CCJ)<\/h4>\n<p>A County Court Judgment (CCJ) is a Court Order that confirms that the debtor has defaulted on payment. A CCJ can be obtained immediately after the expiry date of the County Court Claim. The CCJ is the final decision by the Court which gives you the power to take enforcement action in order to collect the debt.<\/p>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\n\n\t<div id=\"col-412644355\" class=\"col medium-4 small-12 large-4\"  data-animate=\"bounceInLeft\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-inner\"  >\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n<h4>ENFORCEMENT<\/h4>\n<p>Once a County Court Judgment has been obtained, it is then possible to \u2018enforce\u2019 that debt immediately. At IFPC our paralegals will always advise on the most appropriate method of enforcement based on their experience and expertise with similar cases.<\/p>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\n\n\t<div id=\"col-251738925\" class=\"col medium-4 small-12 large-4\"  data-animate=\"bounceInLeft\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-inner\"  >\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n<h4>INSOLVENCY<\/h4>\n<p>Across all stages of debt recovery, insolvency proceedings may be required. If a debtor does not make payment on demand and the debt is not disputed, they are technically deemed insolvent.<\/p>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"panel entry-content\" id=\"tab_letter-before-action\">\n<h4>LETTER BEFORE ACTION<\/h4>\n<p>Before issuing any legal proceedings a letter before action (LBA) should be sent to a debtor. An LBA can be sent for as little as $1.50 plus VAT and on average, 86% of cases result in payment at this stage.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"panel entry-content\" id=\"tab_legal-claim\">\n<h4>LEGAL CLAIM<\/h4>\n<p>\nIf you send a letter before action to your debtor but you do not receive a satisfactory response then the next stage in the legal process is to issue legal proceedings through the County Court. The debtor will be sent a court form requiring them to pay the debt, plus interest and costs within 14 days.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"panel entry-content\" id=\"tab_county-court-judgment-(ccj)\">\n<h4>COUNTY COURT JUDGMENT (CCJ)<\/h4>\n<p>A County Court Judgment (CCJ) is a Court Order that confirms that the debtor has defaulted on payment. A CCJ can be obtained immediately after the expiry date of the County Court Claim. The CCJ is the final decision by the Court which gives you the power to take enforcement action in order to collect the debt.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"panel entry-content\" id=\"tab_enforcement\">\n<h4>ENFORCEMENT<\/h4>\n<p>Once a County Court Judgment has been obtained, it is then possible to \u2018enforce\u2019 that debt immediately. At IFPC our paralegals will always advise on the most appropriate method of enforcement based on their experience and expertise with similar cases.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"panel entry-content\" id=\"tab_insolvency\">\n<h4>INSOLVENCY<\/h4>\n<p>Across all stages of debt recovery, insolvency proceedings may be required. If a debtor does not make payment on demand and the debt is not disputed, they are technically deemed insolvent.<\/p>\n<p>If you are concerned that your debtor may have other creditors chasing payment from them, commencing Winding Up Proceedings against a company or Bankruptcy Proceedings against an individual means you could jump straight to the front of the queue for payment.<\/p>\n<p>Instead of the usual process of issuing a County Court Claim, you can commence insolvency action by initially sending a Draft Winding Up Petition to a company or a Statutory Demand to an individual. On average 81% of cases are paid at this stage without further insolvency proceedings being issued.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\n<style>\n#col-1617446353 > .col-inner {\n  padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\n}\n<\/style>\n\t<\/div>\n\n\t\n<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\t\n<style>\n#section_79201753 {\n  padding-top: 30px;\n  padding-bottom: 30px;\n}\n#section_79201753 .ux-shape-divider--top svg {\n  height: 150px;\n  --divider-top-width: 100%;\n}\n#section_79201753 .ux-shape-divider--bottom svg {\n  height: 150px;\n  --divider-width: 100%;\n}\n<\/style>\n\t<\/section>\n\t\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"page-blank.php","meta":{"footnotes":""},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/ifp.center\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/31"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/ifp.center\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/ifp.center\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/ifp.center\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/ifp.center\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=31"}],"version-history":[{"count":35,"href":"https:\/\/ifp.center\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/31\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":720,"href":"https:\/\/ifp.center\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/31\/revisions\/720"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/ifp.center\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=31"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}